Elverquisst was ruby colored, "distilled from sunshine and rare summer fruits." It was smooth but flecked with gold. It was generally stored in bottles made of transparent crystal, capable of absorbing light. Upon speaking a specific phrase in [[Elven language|Elvish]], the light gathered into thirteen distinct points that resembled the constellation [[Correlian]].

The rare fruits that were used in making elverquisst were [[orosk]]s and [[resmer]]s. As of the [[1372 DR|Year of Wild Magic, 1372 DR]], these plants only grew in [[Evereska]] and a few other isolated valleys around [[Faer√ªn]].{{Cite dragon/267/The New Adventures of Volo: Onward!|81}}

Elverquisst was highly prized by elves, especially in autumn. A ritual was involved in drinking Elverquisst. The ritual involved a chant, pouring the liquid into a goblet, swirling it around, sharing it with others, and offering a ritual bow of the head in thanks.{{Cite organized play/LC/Before Its Time|25}}
